{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#3418: v-for with ref not working as suggested in documentation in some scenarios",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:27:54.589412+00:00",
  "text": "v-for with ref not working as suggested in documentation in some scenarios\n\n### Version\r\n3.0.7\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nOriginal Docs:\r\n```js\r\nimport { onBeforeUpdate, onUpdated } from 'vue'\r\n\r\nexport default {\r\n  setup() {\r\n    let itemRefs = []\r\n    const setItemRef = el => {\r\n      if (el) {\r\n        itemRefs.push(el)\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n    onBeforeUpdate(() => {\r\n      itemRefs = []\r\n    })\r\n    onUpdated(() => {\r\n      console.log(itemRefs)\r\n    })\r\n    return {\r\n      setItemRef\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nFilled array for component lifetime\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nAfter component update array is empty, but lifetime is continue.\r\n\r\n---\r\nTemporary solution:\r\nTip: Only use and export.\r\nAuthors: @NataliaTepluhina\r\n```typescript\r\nfunction useListRef<T>() {\r\n  const elements = ref<T[]>([])\r\n  const active = ref<boolean>(false)\r\n\r\n  watch(active, (isActive) => {\r\n    if (isActive) {\r\n      nextTick(() => active.value = false)\r\n    }\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  function addRef(el) {\r\n    if (!active.value) {\r\n      elements.value = []\r\n      active.value = true\r\n    }\r\n    el && elements.value.push(el)\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  return {\r\n    elements,\r\n    addRef,\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "has workaround"
  ],
